Dear &quot;Doc&quot; Cyr:<br>
I hope that you find some one that you served with and<br>
that all is well in your life.<br>
Let me tell you what good fortune happened to me concerning<br>
finding an old comrade.<br>
first some history<br>
I was a plt corpsman with H 2/26 and later with D 1st Recon<br>
Bn- '69-'70.<br>
We had two Squids in the platoon when I was with the 26ths<br>
Marines. I was an HM3 and my partner &quot;Doc&quot; Paul Card was an<br>
HN. Paul managed to get off a patrol and go to Danang for a<br>
couple of days. Thus, I was the &quot;Doc&quot; in our Platoon for this<br>
particular patrol. At noon we rested outside a ville. The Lt<br>
sent a patrol of 5 men to scout the trail that led into the<br>
Hai Van Mountains. I was one to be the corpsman on this squad<br>
until the Lt realized that he had only one &quot;Doc&quot;,so he kept<br>
me with the rest of the platoon. About 20 minutes later the<br>
squad hit the shit. I did my corpsman thing and went to the<br>
Squads aid. All five were wounded. One died 2 weeks later on<br>
board the USS Repose, Two others were severelly wounded,and<br>
the remaining two were superfical casulities. I did what I <br>
could. My partner &quot;Doc&quot; Card had returned from Danang and <br>
was trying to get back with the platoon the day this <br>
incident occurred. He monitored it over a prc 25. This was<br>
in feb of 1970. Things happened fast. I never really managed<br>
to talk to &quot;Doc&quot; Card about this. Soon after, the colors of<br>
the 26th Marines went home. I was reassigned to Recon and<br>
&quot;Doc&quot; Card was sent to the 5th Marines.<br>
Twenty Two years later my wife tells my about this Robert<br>
Bly and Iron John type of event about Vietnam and Reconcil<br>
lation. And I think boy is this a bunch of crap. But i go<br>
any way. So here we are beating drums and so forth til about<br>
10 pm then there was this candlelit march to the Pacific<br>
ocean. It was pouring rain and really eerie. I ran into a <br>
nam vet friend, Bob Hood, and he told me he brought this guy,<br>
a new member of his church, who was a corpsman in nam. Well,<br>
i m a bit jaded and cynical,so i say &quot;so fuckin what, whats<br>
his name, and where is he?&quot; Bob pointed up a head to the guy<br>
with the black cap and told me his name was Paul Card. I ran<br>
up to him and grabbed him. &quot;Paul Card, PauL fucking Card,&quot;<br>
I yelled in his face. He looked at me like I was nuts. I <br>
my hand in his and said Doc Schwartz Hotel 2/26. Wow! what<br>
a night. Since that time we have become really good friends<br>
but more importantly we helped each other with the emotional<br>
baggage we share as combat corpsman that had fate been a <br>
different that day in feb of 1970 who knows what would have<br>
happened. <br>
just telling it to another squid makes it easier good luck <br>
with your search.<br>
Semper Fi
